layout: layouts/base.njk
title: "Frequently Asked Questions"
description: "Common questions about flooring installation in Corvallis, Independence & the Mid-Willamette Valley. Costs, timelines, materials, and more — answered by Best Practice Flooring."
permalink: /faq/
---

<div class="page-header">
  <h1>Frequently Asked Questions</h1>
  <p>Everything you need to know about flooring installation in the Mid-Willamette Valley.</p>
</div>

<section class="section">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="faq-list">

      <h2 class="faq-category">General</h2>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>What areas do you serve?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>We're based in Independence, Oregon and serve the entire greater Corvallis region. This includes Independence, Monmouth, Dallas, Salem, Corvallis, Albany, Philomath, Adair Village, Lewisburg, Tangent, Jefferson, Stayton, and surrounding Polk and Benton County communities. If you're unsure whether we serve your area, give us a call — we're happy to discuss.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>Do you use subcontractors?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>No. Ake personally installs every floor. We never use subcontractors or day laborers. When you hire Best Practice Flooring, you get the owner on your job site — that means consistent quality, direct communication, and full accountability for the finished product.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>Are you licensed and insured?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Yes. Best Practice Flooring LLC is fully licensed and insured in the state of Oregon. We carry general liability insurance to protect your home during every project. We're happy to provide proof of insurance upon request.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>What payment methods do you accept?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>We accept cash, checks, and credit cards. Payment terms are discussed during the estimate. We never require full payment upfront — typically a deposit to secure your spot on the schedule, with the balance due upon completion.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>Do you do commercial flooring?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Our primary focus is residential flooring installation. However, we're happy to discuss smaller commercial projects like office spaces, retail shops, or rental properties. Give us a call to talk about your commercial project and we'll let you know if it's a good fit.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <h2 class="faq-category">Pricing &amp; Estimates</h2>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>How much does flooring installation cost in the Corvallis area?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Flooring installation costs vary based on the material type, total square footage, subfloor condition, room layout, and any furniture moving or demolition needed. We provide free in-home estimates so you get an accurate, no-obligation price specific to your project. Contact us to schedule a free estimate.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>Do you offer free estimates?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Yes. We provide free in-home estimates for all flooring projects. Ake will visit your home, assess the space, discuss material options, and give you a transparent quote with no hidden fees. There's never any obligation or pressure.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>Do you charge for removing old flooring?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Demolition and removal of existing flooring is included in our estimates when needed. We'll let you know upfront if removal is required and what it will cost — no surprises after work begins.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <h2 class="faq-category">Process &amp; Timeline</h2>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>How long does flooring installation take?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Most single-room installations take 1–2 days. Whole-home flooring projects typically take 3–5 days depending on square footage and material. During your estimate, Ake will give you a clear timeline so you can plan accordingly. We always show up when we say we will.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>Do I need to move my furniture before installation?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>We can move furniture as part of the installation process. However, if you're able to clear smaller items and personal belongings from the room beforehand, it helps us get started faster and protects your valuables. We'll discuss specifics during the estimate.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>What is your installation process?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Our process is straightforward: (1) Free in-home consultation and estimate, (2) Material selection guidance, (3) Scheduling at your convenience, (4) Professional installation by Ake, (5) Final walkthrough to ensure your complete satisfaction. Sarah coordinates scheduling and communication throughout.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>How far in advance do I need to book?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>We typically book 2–3 weeks out, though availability varies by season. Spring and fall are our busiest times. The sooner you call, the sooner we can get you on the schedule. For larger projects, we recommend reaching out at least a month in advance.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>Can I stay in my home during installation?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Yes, in most cases you can stay home during installation. We work room by room and contain dust and debris as much as possible. For whole-home projects, we'll coordinate the schedule so you always have accessible living space. Ake will discuss any special considerations during your estimate.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>How do I prepare my home for flooring installation?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Here's a helpful checklist: (1) Remove small furniture, personal items, and breakables from the work area. (2) Clear closets in rooms being floored. (3) Ensure clear access from the front door to the work area. (4) Secure pets in a separate area. (5) If possible, remove window treatments near floor level. We'll handle moving larger furniture as part of the project.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <h2 class="faq-category">Materials</h2>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>What type of flooring is best for my home?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>The best flooring depends on your lifestyle, budget, and where it's being installed. Hardwood is ideal for living areas and adds home value. LVP is waterproof and great for kitchens, bathrooms, and pet-friendly homes. Tile works best in wet areas and high-traffic zones. Laminate offers a wood look at a lower price point. During your free estimate, Ake will help you choose the right material for each room.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>Do you supply the flooring materials, or do I need to buy them?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Both options are available. We can source materials for you through our supplier relationships, or you can purchase your own materials and we'll install them. Either way, Ake will advise you on quality, quantity, and what to look for to ensure a great result.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>Can you install flooring over existing floors?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>In many cases, yes. Some flooring types like LVP and laminate can be installed over existing hard surfaces if the subfloor is level and in good condition. Ake will assess your current floors during the estimate and recommend the best approach — whether that's installing over or removing the old floor first.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>What's the difference between LVP and laminate?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Both look like real wood, but they're quite different. LVP (luxury vinyl plank) is 100% waterproof and works great in bathrooms, kitchens, and basements. Laminate is water-resistant but not waterproof — standing water can cause damage. LVP is softer underfoot and quieter, while laminate tends to be slightly more affordable. During your estimate, Ake can help you decide which is the best fit for your specific rooms and lifestyle.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>Do you install flooring on stairs?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Yes. Ake installs hardwood, LVP, and laminate on staircases. Stair installation requires specialized cutting and fitting for treads and risers. It's one of the areas where professional installation makes the biggest difference in both appearance and safety.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <h2 class="faq-category">Care &amp; Maintenance</h2>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>How do I maintain my new floors?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Maintenance depends on the material. Hardwood floors should be swept regularly and cleaned with a damp (not wet) mop using a hardwood-specific cleaner. LVP and laminate are low-maintenance — regular sweeping and occasional mopping are sufficient. Tile floors should be cleaned with a pH-neutral cleaner, and grout should be sealed periodically. We provide care instructions specific to your flooring after every installation.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>Do you offer a warranty on your work?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Yes. We stand behind every installation with a workmanship guarantee. If any issue arises related to our installation work, we'll come back and make it right. Material warranties vary by manufacturer and product — we'll explain the specific warranty coverage for your chosen flooring during the estimate.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>What happens if I'm not satisfied with the work?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Your satisfaction is our top priority. We do a final walkthrough with you after every installation to inspect the work together. If anything isn't right, Ake will address it before considering the job complete. Our workmanship guarantee means if an issue related to installation arises later, we'll come back and make it right at no additional charge.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="cta-section">
  <h2>Have More Questions?</h2>
  <p>We're happy to answer anything about your flooring project. Give us a call or send us a message.</p>
  <div class="cta-buttons">
    <a href="/contact/" class="btn btn-primary" style="background:#fff;color:var(--brand-primary);">Contact Us</a>
    <a href="tel:+1{{ site.team.ake.phone }}" class="btn btn-secondary">Call {{ site.team.ake.phoneDisplay }}</a>
  </div>
</section>

